---
description: Testing standards and non-negotiable test coverage rules
alwaysApply: true
---

## TESTING — NON-NEGOTIABLE
- Every new function or feature needs at least one test — no exceptions
- Test negative paths and edge cases, not just the happy path
- For new API endpoints: test auth failure, validation errors, and success
- For new UI flows: test empty state, error state, and success state
- Never suggest merging or committing code with failing tests
- Prefer integration tests over unit tests for critical paths
- Mock external services — tests must not depend on network or third-party APIs
- Test file naming: `*.test.ts` or `*.spec.ts` co-located with the source file

## Bun Test Runner Defaults
- Use `bun test` as the standard command in this workflow.
- Keep tests deterministic: no time-based flakiness, and prefer explicit test fixtures.

## Playwright for End-to-End (Frontend) Flows
- Use Playwright for E2E flows that cross UI + backend boundaries (auth flows, onboarding, checkout).
- For third-party integrations (auth/providers/payments), mock or use test modes so tests are repeatable and offline-safe.

## Database Isolation
- Test DB state should be isolated per test:
  - Prefer transactions/rollbacks for integration tests when possible.
  - Ensure tests do not rely on execution order or leftover seed data.
